<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D5FFFB8FF1DFC43FE49FB7F" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D5FFFB8FF1DFC43FAE1FBCD" blockId="44.[151,1437,906,1257]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5FFFB8FF1DFC43FEFFFC32" bold="true" box="[151,276,906,932]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
males can be diagnosed by following character combination: usually with queliceral projections on anterior region of the distal edge; a prominent, conspicuous and strongly sclerotized ventral tegular process on the tegulum, closely related to the embolus; embolus short, proximally inserted on the tegulum, retrolateral tibial apophysis bifid from base (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5FFFB8FEC4FC3EFE52FB85" box="[334,441,1015,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[272,1303,181,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-27@42.[272,1316,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22A–D. Patrera armata (Chickering, 1940). Male (ICN-Ar-10608): A habitus, dorsal view; B Chelicerae ventral view; C left palp, retroventral view (Arrow: indicates projection basal of the tibia); D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-5481): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; F epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm. C: 1mm; D–F: 0.5mm; G–H: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468433/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Figs 22D</figureCitation>
̅F; 23C̅E; 24E̅G; 25C̅E; 26D̅F; 27D̅F; 28C̅E; 29C̅E). Females are distinguished by having the hood with undulations on the base (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5FFFB8FCA4FBD2FC46FBA3" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[814,941,1051,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chucurui">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5FFFB8FCA4FBD2FC46FBA3" box="[814,941,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P. chucurui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); seminal receptacles absent and posteriorly positioned spermathecae (except in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5FFFB8FDA2FBF6FD43FBCF" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[552,680,1087,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chucurui">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5FFFB8FDA2FBF6FD43FBCF" box="[552,680,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P. chucurui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, anteriorly positioned) (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5FFFB8FC3CFBF6FBC9FBCD" box="[950,1058,1087,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[272,1303,181,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-27@42.[272,1316,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22A–D. Patrera armata (Chickering, 1940). Male (ICN-Ar-10608): A habitus, dorsal view; B Chelicerae ventral view; C left palp, retroventral view (Arrow: indicates projection basal of the tibia); D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-5481): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; F epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; dps, dorsal projection of the subtegulum; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm. C: 1mm; D–F: 0.5mm; G–H: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468433/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Figs 22G</figureCitation>
̅H; 24H̅I; 28F̅G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="207B96733D5FFFB8FF4DFBABFE49FB7F" blockId="44.[151,1437,906,1257]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5FFFB8FF4DFBABFE82FBEA" bold="true" box="[199,361,1122,1148]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Composition:</emphasis>
